title: Winter Intercession
caption: Ongoing
description: Winter Intercession begins on January 3rd, 2023. Most classes meet at UHS with the exception of Directed Studies and Ski/Snowboarding. Please check your Reminds and emails for detailed information regarding your classes. These classes are mandatory, and the time of your selected electives typically runs the length of a normal UHS day. Enjoy your electives!

title: Information Day
caption: January 12th
description:
If you're interested in learning more about University High School for your upcoming 9th grader, this Information Day is perfect for you. We'll discuss the UHS curriculum, what distinguishes UHS, what students typically experience at UHS, and much more. This webinar is online/on Zoom at 4 PM on January 12th, 2023. If you have any questions, please contact the University High School front office (contacts are listed on the 'Home' tab of Phoenikz. 
Webinar ID: 837 6265 8056 
Passcode: 268454

title: Redwood Debate
caption: January 20th
description: The Redwood Debate tournament will be hosted on January 20th and January 21st, 2023 at Bullard High School. The tournament typically lasts until the evening. For any questions, contact Dr. Jarocki or Aubrey Der Torosian.

title: Formal 2023
caption: January 21st
description: The University High School 2023 Formal will be held on January 21st, 2023 from 7 PM - 10 PM. All grade levels may attend but students must not be on the AI List. Tickets will be $35 Pre-Sale, but the price will be raised at the door of the dance. The theme this year is 'Winter Harbor' including harbor-themed decorations, a fog dance floor, and colors of blue, white, and gold (for those that wish to coordinate dress). The dress for this dance is Formal. For any questions, please contact Mr. Benslay or any ASB member.
